 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.1","title":"[audit][transport] Prevent PathSet ID reuse when mixing register() and create_path()","description":"src/transport/aggregator.rs currently leaves PathSet::next_id unchanged when callers manually register() a TransportPath. A subsequent create_path() can therefore reuse an existing PathId (for example after registering PathId(0) into a fresh PathSet) and silently overwrite the earlier entry in the path map. Fix by advancing the monotonic ID cursor on manual registration and add a regression test covering mixed register/create usage.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SwiftDune","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:54:20.802661784Z","created_by":"SwiftDune","updated_at":"2026-03-08T19:33:25.096978850Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T19:33:25.096944707Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in-tree: src/transport/aggregator.rs::PathSet::register() now advances next_id to at least registered_id+1 via compare_exchange loop, and src/transport/aggregator.rs includes regression test test_path_set_register_advances_next_id covering mixed register/create usage. Closing as stale/currently-fixed after source audit; targeted rch validation is being refreshed separately.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:54:20.802661784Z","created_by":"SwiftDune","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.10","title":"[audit][runtime] Validate already-present try_join mutability fix in task_handle/fixtures","description":"The current working tree already contains a local mutability fix for the latest try_join frontier: TaskHandle::try_join now takes &mut self in src/runtime/task_handle.rs, its direct tests now bind mutable handles, and SharedLabHandle::try_join_probe in src/plan/fixtures.rs now temporarily takes a mutable handle before calling try_join(). Validate that this already-present fix clears the intended lib-level compile/lint surface via rch-backed targeted tests plus lib check/clippy, and only edit further if validation exposes a real remaining defect.","notes":"Validated the already-present local mutability fix for the try_join frontier without adding further code edits. Current working tree state already contains: (1) src/runtime/task_handle.rs changing TaskHandle::try_join to take &mut self and updating direct tests to use mutable handles; (2) src/plan/fixtures.rs changing SharedLabHandle::try_join_probe to take a mutable handle before calling try_join(). Validation: rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync --lib try_join_ -- --nocapture => PASS (6 tests passed: runtime::task_handle try_join_* plus related remote_handle_try_join_* coverage); rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync --lib dynamic_lab_join_collects_all_leaves -- --nocapture => PASS; earlier current-tree lib gates also passed via rch: cargo check -p asupersync --lib -q => PASS, cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib --message-format short -- -D warnings => PASS. No additional code change was required from this bead beyond validating the already-present fix.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SageRaven","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:32:15.438236704Z","created_by":"SageRaven","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:38:14.430133153Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:38:14.430028759Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","runtime","verification"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.10","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:32:15.438236704Z","created_by":"SageRaven","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.100","title":"[audit][signal] Preserve one recv() per recorded signal delivery","description":"src/signal/signal.rs tracks monotone delivery counts, but Signal::recv() currently sets seen_deliveries = current and returns a single Some(()) when current > seen_deliveries. If multiple deliveries are recorded before the next recv(), intermediate notifications are collapsed and lost despite the module docs saying no delivered signal notification is lost. Make recv consume exactly one pending delivery per await while preserving cancel safety, add focused regression coverage for multiple injected deliveries, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","notes":"Implementation verified in src/signal/signal.rs: Signal::recv now consumes exactly one pending delivery per await (seen_deliveries = seen_deliveries.saturating_add(1)), and regression signal_recv_preserves_multiple_recorded_deliveries is present. Coordination evidence from CrimsonCompass confirms rch check/clippy pass and reservation released; ownership bookkeeping retained here to close bead cleanly.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MaroonBridge","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-10T18:23:17.501266861Z","created_by":"CrimsonCompass","updated_at":"2026-03-10T18:53:28.848854803Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T18:53:28.795416606Z","close_reason":"Implemented in tree with regression; closeout bookkeeping completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","signal"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.100","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:23:17.501266861Z","created_by":"CrimsonCompass"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.101","title":"[audit][runtime] Give BlockingPool timeout and idle bookkeeping a deterministic time getter","description":"src/runtime/blocking_pool.rs still uses ambient Instant::now()/thread::sleep() for BlockingTaskCompletion::wait_timeout, shutdown_and_wait timeout accounting, and worker idle-retirement timing. That makes timeout/retirement behavior hard to drive deterministically in focused tests and inconsistent with the repo's time-getter pattern already used in other timeout-sensitive modules. Thread explicit time-getter plumbing through the blocking-pool internals so timeout bookkeeping and idle-age calculations can be exercised without wall-clock sleeps, add targeted regressions for wait_timeout/shutdown timeout/idle retirement using synthetic clocks where practical, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldBarn","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:35:08.530013177Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:32:52.459289605Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blocking-pool","determinism","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.101","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:35:08.530013177Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.101","title":"[audit][runtime] Give BlockingPool timeout and idle bookkeeping a deterministic time getter","description":"src/runtime/blocking_pool.rs still uses ambient Instant::now()/thread::sleep() for BlockingTaskCompletion::wait_timeout, shutdown_and_wait timeout accounting, and worker idle-retirement timing. That makes timeout/retirement behavior hard to drive deterministically in focused tests and inconsistent with the repo's time-getter pattern already used in other timeout-sensitive modules. Thread explicit time-getter plumbing through the blocking-pool internals so timeout bookkeeping and idle-age calculations can be exercised without wall-clock sleeps, add targeted regressions for wait_timeout/shutdown timeout/idle retirement using synthetic clocks where practical, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldBarn","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:35:08.530013177Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:47:49.031157108Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T04:47:49.031131892Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in-tree; validated via rch blocking_pool test suite (33 passing) with deterministic time-hook coverage for wait_timeout/shutdown/idle retirement.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blocking-pool","determinism","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.101","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:35:08.530013177Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.102","title":"[audit][transport] Make collect_to_set yield cooperatively on always-ready symbol streams","description":"src/transport/stream.rs still implements CollectToSetFuture::poll as an unbounded loop over poll_next(). On an always-ready SymbolStream, one poll can drain the entire stream and monopolize the executor until EOF or error. Add a bounded per-poll drain budget with self-wake handoff so collect_to_set remains cooperative while preserving dedup/count semantics and early error propagation. Add focused regression coverage for an always-ready symbol stream and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MagentaBear","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-10T18:35:31.645901491Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T19:08:56.001191107Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T19:08:56.001164337Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","fairness","transport"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.102","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:35:31.645901491Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.103","title":"[audit][http] Give Http1Listener bookkeeping a deterministic time getter","description":"src/http/h1/listener.rs still hard-wires ambient wall clock in listener stats and when constructing ShutdownSignal/ConnectionManager. Thread an explicit time_getter through Http1ListenerConfig so accept timestamps, drain deadlines, and connection metadata all follow the configured logical clock, add focused regression tests without sleeping, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BoldPeak","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:37:51.720219201Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T18:55:31.248419146Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T18:55:31.248398227Z","close_reason":"Completed: Http1Listener bookkeeping now uses configurable logical time; lib check/clippy passed remotely; full-workspace gates blocked only by unrelated frontiers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.103","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:37:51.720219201Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.104","title":"[audit][service] Make RetryFuture yield cooperatively on immediate retry loops","description":"src/service/retry.rs can burn through an arbitrary number of retries inside one poll when the cloned service is always-ready, the call future resolves synchronously, and the retry policy future is immediately ready (for example LimitedRetry over a fast-failing service). That lets one executor turn consume the entire retry budget and starve sibling work. Add a bounded per-poll retry budget with self-wake handoff while preserving request cloning, retry ordering, and final result semantics. Add focused regression coverage for always-ready immediate-retry paths and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AzureRobin","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-10T18:38:42.760641757Z","created_by":"AzureRobin","updated_at":"2026-03-10T18:57:31.032650229Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T18:57:17.190032357Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.104","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T18:38:42.760641757Z","created_by":"AzureRobin"}]}
