 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.113","title":"[audit][service] Fail closed when RateLimit::call skips poll_ready reservation","description":"src/service/rate_limit.rs reserves tokens in poll_ready() but call() currently forwards directly to the inner service even when no token was reserved. That lets contract misuse bypass the limiter entirely instead of failing closed, unlike src/service/concurrency_limit.rs which returns LimitExceeded on the same misuse. Harden RateLimit::call so unreserved calls return RateLimitExceeded immediately without touching the inner service, preserve the existing reserved-token panic-restore behavior, and add a focused regression proving call-without-poll_ready neither consumes the inner service nor bypasses the limiter.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentCastle","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-10T23:22:00.234991827Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T00:10:11.726194407Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T00:10:11.726168589Z","close_reason":"Implemented fail-closed RateLimit::call misuse path with regression; targeted rch cargo test rate_limit --lib passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","rate-limit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.113","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:22:00.234991827Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.114","title":"[audit][runtime] Prevent DeadlineMonitor panic when checkpoint instant is ahead of monitor clock","description":"DeadlineMonitor::check currently computes wall_no_progress via now_instant.duration_since(entry.last_progress). entry.last_progress is seeded from checkpoint_state.last_checkpoint, so if a checkpoint instant is ahead of the monitor time source (custom/non-monotonic getter, synthetic test clocks, or mixed clock domains), check() can panic. Make no-progress elapsed calculations saturating and add a focused regression that seeds a future checkpoint instant and verifies check() does not panic.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ScarletSparrow","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:24:12.431489264Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T23:31:42.312593832Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T23:30:40.816847938Z","close_reason":"Implemented saturating elapsed hardening + regressions; full cargo test blocked by unrelated E0277 frontier in src/service/rate_limit.rs","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.114","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:24:12.431489264Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2489,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.114","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Implemented in src/runtime/deadline_monitor.rs: replaced two Instant::duration_since sites with saturating_duration_since to prevent panic on forward-skew/non-monotonic custom clocks (check interval wall-elapsed + no-progress wall elapsed). Added regressions no_warning_when_checkpoint_instant_is_ahead_of_monitor_clock and check_interval_tolerates_time_getter_going_backwards. Local rustfmt --check on this file passes. rch-offloaded cargo test for the new tests is currently blocked at workspace compile frontier by an unrelated pre-existing error: src/service/rate_limit.rs E0277 (<S as Service<Request>>::Error: Unpin bound mismatch).","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:30:06Z"},{"id":2490,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.114","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Post-implementation polish: replaced test Duration::from_secs(120/60) with Duration::from_mins(2/1) to satisfy clippy::duration_suboptimal_units on deadline_monitor test additions.","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:31:42Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.115","title":"[audit][cx/runtime] Remove ambient wall-clock checkpoint timestamps from Cx progress tracking","description":"Cx::checkpoint() and Cx::checkpoint_with() currently record CheckpointState timestamps via Instant::now() in src/types/task_context.rs. That bypasses the runtime time abstraction, adds an undocumented ambient-authority edge in core Cx state, and makes checkpoint-driven diagnostics/deadline-monitor metadata depend on wall clock instead of explicit runtime time semantics. Thread checkpoint timestamps through explicit Time values (prefer timer-driver/logical runtime time, with wall-clock fallback only at the boundary provider), update deadline-monitor state/tests accordingly, and tighten ambient-authority coverage so this regression is caught.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GreenReef","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:26:55.057545330Z","created_by":"GreenReef","updated_at":"2026-03-10T23:46:07.543687742Z","closed_at":"2026-03-10T23:46:07.543661803Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","cx","determinism","runtime","time"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.115","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:26:55.057545330Z","created_by":"GreenReef"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.116","title":"[audit][service] Make Reconnect::call fail closed when no connection is ready","description":"src/service/reconnect.rs currently panics with expect(\"poll_ready must be called before call\") when Reconnect::call() is used while the wrapper is lazy/disconnected and no inner service is present. That turns a recoverable readiness misuse into a hard library panic. Harden the call path to fail closed with a typed ReconnectError instead of panicking, keep stale-call refresh semantics intact, add focused regressions for lazy/disconnected call misuse, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkDune","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:32:14.408936487Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-10T23:32:14.408936487Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.116","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:32:14.408936487Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.116","title":"[audit][service] Make Reconnect::call fail closed when no connection is ready","description":"src/service/reconnect.rs currently panics with expect(\"poll_ready must be called before call\") when Reconnect::call() is used while the wrapper is lazy/disconnected and no inner service is present. That turns a recoverable readiness misuse into a hard library panic. Harden the call path to fail closed with a typed ReconnectError instead of panicking, keep stale-call refresh semantics intact, add focused regressions for lazy/disconnected call misuse, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BlueIsland","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:32:14.408936487Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:08:31.042698145Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.116","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:32:14.408936487Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.117","title":"[audit][server] Make ShutdownSignal::new capture a stable time source","description":"src/server/shutdown.rs currently uses a default time getter that consults Cx::current() on every clock read. That lets a single ShutdownSignal mix virtual and wall time depending on which thread or phase touches it, so begin_drain/collect_stats/deadline waiting can silently change basis after construction. Capture a stable time source when ShutdownSignal::new() is created (timer driver if present, otherwise wall clock), keep with_time_getter for explicit overrides, update connection-manager waiting if needed, and add focused regressions proving shutdown timing stays on the captured clock even after the ambient Cx is gone.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrownTower","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-10T23:46:48.809108705Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T00:00:27.422488960Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T00:00:27.422464355Z","close_reason":"Implemented: stable ShutdownSignal time source; targeted tests, cargo check, and lib clippy green","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","server","time"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.117","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-10T23:46:48.809108705Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.118","title":"[audit][service] Reset reserved rate-limit tokens on clone so clones cannot spend another handle's reservation","description":"src/service/rate_limit.rs clones reserved_tokens into new RateLimit handles. If one handle successfully poll_ready() reserves a token and is then cloned before call(), the clone inherits that reservation and can call() without performing its own readiness check. That duplicates a single reservation across multiple handles and violates the fail-closed reservation model already used elsewhere (for example Buffer's clone-local ready reservation). Reset clone-local reserved token state on clone and add a regression proving a clone cannot spend another handle's reservation.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"QuietMarsh","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:09.017767621Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:09.017767621Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.118","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:09.017767621Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.119","title":"[audit][trace] Bind ReplayCheckpoint validation to full trace identity","description":"ReplayCheckpoint currently validates resume targets with only seed/version/config_hash plus an events_processed<=total_events check. That allows a checkpoint from one trace to resume against a different trace that reuses the same seed/config hash but differs in recorded_at, description, or total event count. Tighten checkpoint identity so resume fails closed when those metadata dimensions differ, add focused regressions for same-seed metadata drift and event-count drift, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MistyMoose","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:25.044057087Z","created_by":"MistyMoose","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:25.044057087Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","replay","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.119","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:25.044057087Z","created_by":"MistyMoose"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.118","title":"[audit][service] Make rate-limit clone reservation regression compile and verify clone-local semantics","description":"src/service/rate_limit.rs clones reserved_tokens into new RateLimit handles. If one handle successfully poll_ready() reserves a token and is then cloned before call(), the clone inherits that reservation and can call() without performing its own readiness check. That duplicates a single reservation across multiple handles and violates the fail-closed reservation model already used elsewhere (for example Buffer's clone-local ready reservation). Reset clone-local reserved token state on clone and add a regression proving a clone cannot spend another handle's reservation.","notes":"Reality check: the branch already contained the semantic fix where RateLimit clone resets reserved_tokens to 0 and the regression body. My live code delta is adding derive Clone, Copy to test EchoService so svc.clone() compiles, then validating the regression and targeted checks via rch.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"QuietMarsh","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:09.017767621Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:59:37.609754952Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T04:59:37.609730206Z","close_reason":"Completed: existing clone-local reservation fix verified; regression harness repaired by deriving Clone, Copy for EchoService; validated with rch cargo check/clippy/test.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.118","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:09.017767621Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.119","title":"[audit][trace] Bind ReplayCheckpoint validation to full trace identity","description":"ReplayCheckpoint currently validates resume targets with only seed/version/config_hash plus an events_processed<=total_events check. That allows a checkpoint from one trace to resume against a different trace that reuses the same seed/config hash but differs in recorded_at, description, or total event count. Tighten checkpoint identity so resume fails closed when those metadata dimensions differ, add focused regressions for same-seed metadata drift and event-count drift, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"MistyMoose","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:46.697451177Z","created_by":"MistyMoose","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:46.697451177Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","replay","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.119","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:33:46.697451177Z","created_by":"MistyMoose","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.12","title":"[audit][tests] Remove stale mutable receiver bindings in channel partition injection tests","description":"The current rch-backed 'cargo clippy -p asupersync --tests --message-format short --keep-going -- -D warnings' frontier reports three stale bindings in tests/channel_partition_injection.rs where receivers were made mutable during prior mutability repairs but are no longer read. Clean those bindings up so the test target is warning-free again, validate with targeted rch-backed check/clippy/test for channel_partition_injection, and keep the scope limited to that file.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:49:40.293165217Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:54:54.837278970Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:54:54.837257971Z","close_reason":"Completed: cleaned tests/channel_partition_injection.rs by keeping mutable receiver bindings only in tests that actually read from the channel and changing the three dead receiver bindings to _rx at the cancellation/evidence/stats sites; validation: rustfmt --check --edition 2024 tests/channel_partition_injection.rs, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-partition-check12b cargo check --test channel_partition_injection, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-partition-clippy12b cargo clippy --test channel_partition_injection -- -D warnings, and rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-partition-test12b cargo test --test channel_partition_injection -- --nocapture all passed remotely","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.12","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:49:40.293165217Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
