-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.121","title":"[audit][signal] Make GracefulBuilder grace-period timing deterministic","description":"src/signal/graceful.rs hardcodes wall_now() inside GracefulBuilder::run() when it enters the grace-period timeout path, even though the same module already exposes GracePeriodGuard::with_time_getter() for deterministic/synthetic clocks. That leaves graceful-shutdown timeout behavior pinned to wall-clock progression, makes focused tests depend on real time, and is inconsistent with the repo’s explicit time-source seams in other timeout-sensitive code. Thread an explicit time-getter/config seam through GracefulBuilder/GracefulConfig (and any needed timeout helper support), add targeted deterministic regressions for complete-within-grace and timeout-after-grace without wall-clock sleeps, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WindyGrove","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:34:09.387330954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:34:09.387330954Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","signal","time"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.121","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:34:09.387330954Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.121","title":"[audit][signal] Make GracefulBuilder grace-period timing deterministic","description":"src/signal/graceful.rs hardcodes wall_now() inside GracefulBuilder::run() when it enters the grace-period timeout path, even though the same module already exposes GracePeriodGuard::with_time_getter() for deterministic/synthetic clocks. That leaves graceful-shutdown timeout behavior pinned to wall-clock progression, makes focused tests depend on real time, and is inconsistent with the repo’s explicit time-source seams in other timeout-sensitive code. Thread an explicit time-getter/config seam through GracefulBuilder/GracefulConfig (and any needed timeout helper support), add targeted deterministic regressions for complete-within-grace and timeout-after-grace without wall-clock sleeps, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WindyGrove","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:34:09.387330954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:08:31.011848339Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T05:08:31.011821770Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","signal","time"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.121","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:34:09.387330954Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2492,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.121","author":"WindyGrove","text":"Implemented optional custom Time getter support for GracefulConfig/GracefulBuilder and routed GracefulBuilder::run() through TimeoutFuture::with_time_getter only when a custom getter is present; default wall-clock/fallback timeout path remains unchanged. Added deterministic manual-poll regressions for completion-within-grace and timeout-after-grace without wall-clock sleeps. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-windygrove-grace-tests cargo test graceful_builder_run_