+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.122","title":"[audit][service] Make LoadShed::call fail closed until readiness is observed","description":"src/service/load_shed.rs currently forwards requests to the inner service whenever overloaded is false, even if the caller never polled readiness first. That lets call() bypass the load-shedding contract entirely on fresh wrappers or after a consumed readiness window, unlike sibling middleware (ConcurrencyLimit, RateLimit, and now Reconnect) that fail closed on readiness misuse. Harden LoadShed::call() so it only dispatches after an observed poll_ready, return a typed readiness error instead of silently invoking the inner service, preserve real overload shedding semantics, add focused regressions for call-without-poll_ready and readiness-consumption behavior, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrightIsland","estimated_minutes":90,"created_at":"2026-03-11T04:35:29.398391903Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T04:52:24.874327118Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T04:52:24.874296300Z","close_reason":"Implemented fail-closed LoadShed readiness contract; remote load_shed tests passed; isolated remote clippy -p asupersync --lib exited 0; workspace fmt/clippy artifact retrieval issues remain unrelated","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.122","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:35:29.398391903Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.123","title":"[audit][service] Keep LoadBalancer dispatches on the stored backend instance","description":"LoadBalancer::call_balanced currently probes readiness on a cloned backend and then dispatches through that clone. Because the stored backend instance is never mutated, per-backend mutable state and readiness transitions can be reset on every request. This breaks stateful services whose readiness or capacity lives in the service value itself rather than behind shared Arcs.\n\nPatch src/service/load_balance.rs so readiness probing and call construction operate on the stored backend instance, preserving backend-local state across requests. Add focused regressions for a single-use/stateful backend that should accept one request and reject the next, and validate with rch-offloaded cargo checks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CopperFalcon","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:40:12.488332815Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:04:35.983359155Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T05:04:35.983336153Z","close_reason":"Completed: LoadBalancer now dispatches on stored backend state; regression test and remote check pass; global clippy blocked by unrelated rate_limit lane","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","load-balance","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.123","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:40:12.488332815Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2491,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.123","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"[2026-03-11 CopperFalcon] Fixed src/service/load_balance.rs so LoadBalancer::call_balanced() no longer probes and dispatches through an ephemeral backend clone. Backends are now stored behind per-backend mutexes and call_balanced() probes readiness plus constructs the request future on the stored backend instance, preserving backend-local mutable state/readiness across requests while keeping self-wake repoll handling and load-metric rollback on panic/drop. Added regression test lb_call_balanced_preserves_backend_local_state covering a single-use backend that must reject a second request once its internal state is consumed. Validation: (1) rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-copper-test-123 cargo test -p asupersync --lib lb_call_balanced_preserves_backend_local_state -- --nocapture => PASS. (2) rch exec -- env CARGO_INCREMENTAL=0 CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-copper-check-123 cargo check --all-targets => remote exit=0. (3) rustfmt --check src/service/load_balance.rs => PASS locally. (4) full rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings is currently blocked by unrelated src/service/rate_limit.rs:961 clippy::redundant_clone in QuietMarsh's claimed lane; no clippy findings were produced for the touched load_balance surface before that blocker.","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:04:03Z"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.124","title":"[audit][service] Make Hedge::call fail closed until readiness is observed","description":"src/service/hedge.rs currently forwards requests directly in Hedge::call without requiring a prior successful poll_ready. That can violate inner Service readiness contracts and allows call() to run on wrappers that were never observed ready. Harden Hedge with clone-local readiness tracking so call() fails closed when readiness was not observed (or already consumed), add a typed NotReady error variant, add regressions for call-without-poll_ready and readiness-consumption behavior, and validate with rch-offloaded cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldBarn","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:57:40.381416868Z","created_by":"EmeraldBarn","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:31:37.721294655Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T05:31:37.721268236Z","close_reason":"Implemented fail-closed Hedge readiness contract (NotReady path), added clone-local readiness tracking, and added regressions for no-poll_ready, readiness consumption, and clone inheritance; validated via rch check/clippy and focused hedge tests.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","hedge","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.124","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T04:57:40.381416868Z","created_by":"EmeraldBarn"}]}
