+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.126","title":"[audit][service] Route Steer readiness through the chosen backend instead of probing all backends","description":"src/service/steer.rs currently calls poll_ready() on every backend even though each call() dispatches to exactly one chosen backend. That fan-out can strand stateful readiness reservations (permits/slots/tokens) on backends that were not selected, and it also lets the least-ready backend backpressure unrelated routes. Rework Steer so request-specific readiness is handled through the chosen backend only, add focused regressions for stateful backends whose reservations must not be stranded, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","notes":"Implemented in src/service/steer.rs. Reworked Steer to route readiness through a chosen-backend SteerFuture instead of probing all backends in poll_ready(); inner services now live behind Arc<parking_lot::Mutex<_>> so the selected backend retains mutable state across requests without stranding readiness reservations on unselected peers. Added focused regressions for selected-backend-only reservation and for ready routes not being blocked by unrelated pending backends. Validation: rch cargo fmt --check is currently blocked by unrelated formatting drift in src/net/unix/split.rs, src/service/hedge.rs, src/service/load_balance.rs, src/service/timeout.rs, and test_tokio_watch/src/main.rs. UBS rust-only scan on src/service/steer.rs reported formatting/clippy/cargo-check/test-build clean for the touched file; its remaining warnings are heuristic panic/expect reports, including the conventional poll-after-completion panic surface already used across the service layer. An rch-offloaded cargo test run was started for steer_* tests but did not yield a final result before session handoff.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CloudyWillow","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:02:44.286324419Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:13:53.259913092Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.126","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:02:44.286324419Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.127","title":"[audit][service] Make Filter::call fail closed until readiness is observed","description":"src/service/filter.rs forwards accepted requests straight into inner.call() without requiring prior poll_ready() success. That lets callers bypass the wrapper readiness contract and can drive stateful inner services without a reserved ready window. Harden Filter with clone-local readiness tracking so each successful poll_ready() authorizes exactly one call, fail closed with a typed error on misuse, add focused regressions for call-without-poll_ready, consumed readiness, and clone isolation, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:05:45.686716751Z","created_by":"BrightIsland","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:09:56.513771532Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T05:09:56.513744572Z","close_reason":"Implemented fail-closed Filter readiness contract; remote lib check passed; filtered lib tests passed; isolated clippy blocked by unrelated steer.rs warnings","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.127","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:05:45.686716751Z","created_by":"BrightIsland"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.128","title":"[audit][service] Avoid stranding inner readiness reservations behind ConcurrencyLimit capacity waits","description":"src/service/concurrency_limit.rs currently polls inner.poll_ready() before it has actually claimed outer semaphore capacity. When the limiter has no capacity, that can strand inner readiness reservations behind outer backpressure, especially for stateful services whose poll_ready() reserves a permit/slot/token until call(). Reorder readiness handling so the limiter never consults inner readiness while it is still waiting on outer capacity, keep capacity accounting correct when inner later reports Pending/Error, add focused regressions for the stranded-reservation case, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrightIsland","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:14:57.762860325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:25:47.601425508Z","closed_at":"2026-03-11T05:25:47.601398328Z","close_reason":"Completed: ConcurrencyLimit now acquires/releases outer capacity without polling inner while capacity is unavailable; focused rch check/test/clippy passed.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.128","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:14:57.762860325Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.129","title":"[audit][trace] Make CrashPackBuilder::build fail closed when failure metadata is missing","description":"src/trace/crashpack.rs currently panics with expect(\"CrashPackBuilder requires a failure\") when a caller reaches CrashPackBuilder::build() without setting failure metadata. That turns a recoverable builder misuse into a hard library panic. Change the builder to fail closed with a typed build error instead of panicking, update internal/runtime and contract call sites to handle the fallible build path explicitly, add focused regressions for missing-failure and successful builds, and validate with rch-backed cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WindyGrove","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:30:23.201780074Z","created_by":"WindyGrove","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:30:23.201780074Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.129","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:30:23.201780074Z","created_by":"WindyGrove"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.13","title":"[audit][tests] Remove lock-guard drop extension in shared handle join probe","description":"The current rch-backed 'cargo clippy -p asupersync --tests --message-format short --keep-going -- -D warnings' frontier reports tests/shared_handle_test.rs:73:42 for a temporary with significant Drop in a match scrutinee. Refactor the join-probe branch so the handle lock and try_join call happen outside the match scrutinee, preserving behavior while satisfying clippy. Validate with targeted rch-backed check/clippy/test for shared_handle_test and keep the scope limited to that file.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:55:24.106180172Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","updated_at":"2026-03-08T04:59:15.854236082Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T04:59:15.854217358Z","close_reason":"Completed: refactored tests/shared_handle_test.rs SharedLabHandle::try_join_probe so the handle lock and try_join call occur outside the match scrutinee, preserving ready/none/error behavior while removing the significant_drop_in_scrutinee clippy error; validation: rustfmt --check --edition 2024 tests/shared_handle_test.rs, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-shared-check13 cargo check --test shared_handle_test, rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-shared-clippy13 cargo clippy --test shared_handle_test -- -D warnings, and rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-target-ivoryelk-shared-test13 cargo test --test shared_handle_test -- --nocapture all reached remote exit 0","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.13","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T04:55:24.106180172Z","created_by":"IvoryElk","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.130","title":"[audit][service] Make Timeout::call fail closed unless readiness was observed","description":"src/service/timeout.rs currently forwards call() directly to inner.call(req) without enforcing that a successful poll_ready() was observed first. For wrappers around stateful/strict inner services, call() misuse can panic or violate readiness contracts instead of failing closed with a typed error. Add explicit readiness gating so each successful poll_ready authorizes exactly one call, return a typed NotReady error on misuse, add focused regressions that prove call-without-poll_ready fails closed and does not invoke inner, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"OrangeForge","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:53:27.665345340Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-11T05:53:27.665345340Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.130","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-11T05:53:27.665345340Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.14","title":"[audit][service] Respect DNS poll interval after resolution failures","description":"DnsServiceDiscovery::poll_discover() increments error_count on resolve failure but leaves last_resolve unchanged. When a hostname is failing, repeated poll_discover() calls therefore retry DNS immediately on every poll instead of honoring poll_interval, which can create hot-loop retry pressure in callers that poll frequently. Fix by recording the failure attempt time, preserving deterministic diff behavior for successful resolutions, and adding a regression test that proves repeated failures within the interval do not increment error_count again until the interval elapses or invalidate() is called.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ScarletRaven","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-08T18:41:46.886779808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T19:36:05.520817992Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T19:36:05.520798145Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in-tree and released by assignee: src/service/discover.rs now records last_resolve on DNS resolution failure, and the file includes regressions dns_discovery_failed_resolution_respects_poll_interval plus dns_discovery_invalidate_forces_retry_after_failed_resolution. ScarletRaven reported rch-backed cargo check -p asupersync --lib and cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings passing on this slice; narrowed test-target runs remained stuck in the known rch queue/post-run transport path, with no concrete failing output surfaced.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.14","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T18:41:46.886779808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.15","title":"[audit][browser-reactor] Stop wake() from fabricating readiness without host signals","description":"BrowserReactor::wake() currently snapshots every registered token's interest mask into the pending event queue. That violates the Reactor::wake() contract in src/runtime/reactor/mod.rs, which says wake() should only break poll() out early and must not invent I/O readiness. In the browser scaffold this means a plain wake can report false READABLE/WRITABLE readiness for unrelated tokens before any host callback calls notify_ready(). Fix wake() so host readiness flows only through notify_ready(), keep coalescing semantics sane, and add deterministic regressions proving wake() with registered tokens yields no synthetic readiness while notify_ready() still works.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentSpring","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:24:27.806591954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T22:31:50.427623508Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T22:31:50.427598282Z","close_reason":"Completed: BrowserReactor wake no longer fabricates readiness; targeted browser-reactor tests pass via rch; cargo check --all-targets passes via rch; workspace clippy still fails in unrelated transport/blocking_pool files.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","reactor","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.15","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:24:27.806591954Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
